This paper is primarily focused on image recognition using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of weight sharing to reduce the number of parameters in the network, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for improving convolutional network architectures, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on multiple datasets, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
